<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('partials/head', { title: 'Privacy Policy · websidian' }) %>
</head>
<body class="landing-page">
  <header class="landing-nav">
    <a class="landing-brand" href="/">websidian</a>
    <nav class="landing-nav-actions">
      <select class="lang-select" data-lang-switch aria-label="Language" data-i18n-attr="aria-label:lang_switch">
        <option value="en">EN</option>
        <option value="de">DE</option>
      </select>
      <a class="btn-ghost" href="/" data-i18n="home">Home</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main class="landing-main">
    <article class="legal">
      <h1 data-i18n="pp_title">Privacy Policy</h1>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_s1_h">1. General</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pp_s1_p1">
          Websidian is an open-source online service designed to process as little
          personal data as possible.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_s2_h">2. User Account</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pp_s2_p1">A user account is required to use the service.</p>
        <p data-i18n="pp_s2_p2">Only the following data is stored:</p>
        <ul>
          <li data-i18n="pp_s2_li1">freely chosen username</li>
          <li data-i18n="pp_s2_li2">password hash (no plaintext password)</li>
          <li data-i18n="pp_s2_li3">mandatory two-factor authentication data</li>
          <li data-i18n="pp_s2_li4">encrypted connection details for the storage you connect (host, keys) — stored encrypted, never in plaintext</li>
        </ul>
        <p data-i18n="pp_s2_p3">
          Registration with an email address or real name is not required.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_s3_h">3. Content and Encryption</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pp_s3_p1">
          All user data is encrypted by default using end-to-end encryption (E2E).
        </p>
        <p data-i18n="pp_s3_p2">
          The operator has no access to unencrypted user content.
        </p>
        <p data-i18n="pp_s3_p3">
          Decryption takes place exclusively on the users&rsquo; devices.
        </p>
        <p data-i18n="pp_s3_p4">
          Your files are stored on the storage provider you connect yourself
          (e.g. your own S3 bucket or WebDAV/Nextcloud server) — not by
          websidian. websidian holds no copy of your files; it only stores the
          connection credentials for that storage, encrypted at rest.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_s4_h">4. Technical Data</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pp_s4_p1">
          The service only processes technical data that is strictly necessary for its
          operation.
        </p>
        <p data-i18n="pp_s4_p2">
          No permanent storage of IP addresses or similar access data takes place.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_s5_h">5. Donations</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pp_s5_p1">
          websidian is a non-profit project. Voluntary donations are optional and
          handled entirely by an external provider (e.g. PayPal).
        </p>
        <p data-i18n="pp_s5_p2">
          websidian does not process or store any payment or credit-card data.
        </p>
        <p data-i18n="pp_s5_p3">The donation provider&rsquo;s own privacy policy applies.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_s6_h">6. Data Security</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pp_s6_p1">
          The service uses technical and organizational security measures, in
          particular:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li data-i18n="pp_s6_li1">end-to-end encryption of all content</li>
          <li data-i18n="pp_s6_li2">encrypted database storage</li>
          <li data-i18n="pp_s6_li3">mandatory two-factor authentication</li>
          <li data-i18n="pp_s6_li4">modern authentication methods</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_s7_h">7. Data Deletion</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pp_s7_p1">
          Users may delete their account and all associated data at any time, unless
          technical or legal restrictions apply.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_s8_h">8. User Rights</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pp_s8_p1">
          Under applicable data protection law, users have in particular the right to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li data-i18n="pp_s8_li1">access</li>
          <li data-i18n="pp_s8_li2">rectification</li>
          <li data-i18n="pp_s8_li3">erasure</li>
          <li data-i18n="pp_s8_li4">restriction of processing</li>
          <li data-i18n="pp_s8_li5">complaint to a data protection authority</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_s9_h">9. Contact</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pp_s9_p1">
          Inquiries regarding data protection can be submitted via the contact address
          provided in the imprint.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
